Description: Add package metadata for undici-types during Noble builds
 Debian node-undici installs the upstream types directory as undici-types, but
 the source tree does not include a package.json in types/. Ubuntu Noble's
 @types/node imports undici-types during TypeScript builds, so dh-nodejs needs
 package metadata to link the in-tree component at build time.
Forwarded: not-needed

--- /dev/null
+++ b/types/package.json
@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@
+{
+  "name": "undici-types",
+  "version": "7.3.0",
+  "description": "A stand-alone types package for Undici",
+  "license": "MIT",
+  "types": "index.d.ts",
+  "files": ["*.d.ts"]
+}
